# Brightness Analysis of a Distant Galaxy

## Problem Definition
This project estimates the true brightness (μ) of a celestial object and the noise level (σ) from noisy observations using Bayesian inference and MCMC.

## Data
Synthetic observations were generated from a normal distribution with:
- true_mu = 150.0
- true_sigma = 10.0
- n_obs = 50

## Method
The posterior distribution was sampled using the `emcee` MCMC library.
The model includes:
- Gaussian log-likelihood
- Uniform prior on μ in (0, 300)
- Uniform prior on σ in (0, 50)

## Results
Include your final median values, percentile intervals, and absolute errors.

## Discussion
Comment on:
- Accuracy of μ
- Why μ is estimated more precisely than σ
- Correlation pattern in the corner plot
- Effect of narrow prior
- Effect of reducing n_obs to 5